                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13189959" author="mbenson" created="Fri, 20 Jan 2012 18:09:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is a convention within JXPath code that the empty namespace be represented as a Java &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt;.  Rather than check for &lt;tt&gt;&quot;&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; at the point you identified, I have elected to modify DOMNodePointer to translate &lt;tt&gt;&quot;&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt; when returning its result.  In this manner JXPath&apos;s DOM handling will function in the same manner as its JDOM handling, and any other callers of the method will be fixed as well.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1234036.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13192085" author="hdalmeid" created="Tue, 24 Jan 2012 12:23:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks a lot, I build the current 1.4 from svn and it fixes our case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
